cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with optimization of bit mappings for soft forward error correction, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of fiber-optical communication systems, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Similar to the previous point, the paper deals with improving the performance of communication systems, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper mentions the use of low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes, which are a type of error-correcting code that can be analyzed using graph-based algorithms. This falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing the performance of a communication system, which can be viewed as a control system. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
